in the shower?

13
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:45,345
- No.
- Good.

14
00:02:45,580 --> 00:02:46,263
Why?

15
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,662
No reason.
Mckenzie might cancel.

16
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:50,231
Nobody's going to cancel.

17
00:02:50,460 --> 00:02:52,462
Or reschedule.
It's happened before.

18
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:55,465
Sara called last night.
They sold their apartment.

19
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:58,101
Already? They put it up for sale
last month.

20
00:02:58,940 --> 00:03:01,261
They cut the price in half
to sell faster.

21
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:04,265
Luisa, our kids were born
in this house.

22
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,025
Where would we live?

23
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:08,831
We could live with my parents
in Mexico.

24
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:10,505
With your parents?

25
00:03:10,740 --> 00:03:13,266
You want me to move to Mexico
and live with your parents?

26
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:16,071
You could get a good job
with your resume.

27
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:17,187
And the kids?

28
00:03:17,420 --> 00:03:19,661
They can go to college there.

29
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:21,390
College.

30
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,185
That's another thing.

31
00:03:23,780 --> 00:03:26,704
How will we afford it?
Unemployment won't cover it.

32
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:28,951
