see you yet.You can wait here.

95
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:22,383
Sure.

96
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:24,381
Thanks.

97
00:07:44,220 --> 00:07:46,826
Excuse me, can I get some coffee
somewhere?

98
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:48,585
Yes, downstairs on the right.

99
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:58,781
Hey, David.

100
00:08:00,860 --> 00:08:02,021
Where are you going?

101
00:08:02,260 --> 00:08:04,069
I'm a friend of David's.
I was saying hi.

102
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:05,461
One moment, please.

103
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:08,590
I'm here to see the president
and I'm a little early...

104
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:12,267
Mr. Solar is very busy.
He mustn't be disturbed.

105
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,426
- Wait there.
- Right.

106
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:18,142
Okay.

107
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:31,226
Hey, Sole!

108
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:32,541
Hi, Martin.

109
00:08:35,580 --> 00:08:38,345
Let's get lunch.
I reserved at a Chinese place.

110
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,143
I'm almost done with this screen!

111
00:08:42,380 --> 00:08:43,791
You've been at it all morning.

112
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:45,465
That's the easiest level.

113
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:47,862
I ate the magic mushroom!

114
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:51,422
Forget the mushroom,
you're on the easy level.

115
00:08:51,660 --> 00:08:54,664
I'll go and get a cup of coffee.
Thank you.

116
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:55,503
Shut up!

117
00:09:12,180 --> 00:09:13,102
Hello?

118
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:15,468
Hey, I missed you on Saturday.

119
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:17,270
You were right not to go.
We lost, as usual.

120
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,387
Finally.

121
00:09:18,620 --> 00:09:19,746
Roberto Gomez.

122
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:21,027
Oh, I'm sorry.

123
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:22,864
Don't worry about it.

124
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,590
The president is waiting.

125
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:29,144
Okay, see you later.
Bye.

126
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:33,585
Everybody out.

127
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:51,025
- How is everything, Roberto?
- Javier.

128
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,347
What happened to you?

129
00:09:52,580 --> 00:09:55,265
In the cafeteria, a disaster.
Never mind.

130
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,821
- How are you?
- Couldn't be better.

131
00:09:58,260 --> 00:10:00,262
Hey, nice office, huh?

132
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:02,389
Yeah.
How are Luisa and the kids?

133
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:04,429
Great. Luisa's doing great.

134
00:10:04,660 --> 00:10:08,710
Chasing kids around all day...
Anyway, we're fine.

135
00:10:08,940 --> 00:10:11,341
- Is she still teaching?
- Not at the moment.

136
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:13,628
She substitutes sometimes,
stuff like that.

137
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:16,386
My daughter's in New York,
at N.Y.U.

138
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:20,261
50 grand a year and another 50 grand
for the apartment in Tribeca.

139
00:10:20,740 --> 00:10:23,061
- Those are big numbers.
- But you know what?

140
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:24,506
I don't care.

141
00:10:25,260 --> 00:10:28,628
Your kids' future is worth it,
don't you think?

142
00:10:28,860 --> 00:10:31,181
Nothing better to spend it on.
Of course.

143
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:33,509
What can I do for you?

144
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,264
Well, Javier, look.

145
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,264
I'll fill you in.
I've been working

146
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:42,471
freelance these last few years.
No attachments, rig ht?

147
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:45,749
Taking my time,
charging my battery...

148
00:10:45,980 --> 00:10:47,664
And I feel like I'm ready

149
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:50,221
to settle down.
You came to mind and I thought

150
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:54,784
I'd be perfect for your new project
So here I am.

151
00:11:05,540 --> 00:11:09,101
Javier, the truth is
I'm having a hard time.

152
00:11:09,420 --> 00:11:10,865
I need a job.

153
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:16,901
A job, a job, a job

154
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:20,030
I can't offer you a job, Roberto.

155
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:22,706
You know things aren't that simple.

156
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:26,706
Tell me about it. I've been jobless
for two years with a mortgage to pay

157
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:30,262
and Luisa has no idea
we'll be broke in two months.

158
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:34,183
It doesn't have to be full time.

159
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:38,263
I could come in a couple times a week
How about it?

160
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,865
Impossible.

161
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,511
I could easily swing it

162
00:11:42,740 --> 00:11:45,630
but you know I can't
because you're my friend

163
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:48,429
But I'm good.

164
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,504
I'm good, Javier.

165
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:52,982
Okay, maybe not as good as before.

166
00:11:53,220 --> 00:11:55,871
But remember, the Coca-Cola campaign
was my idea.

167
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:57,625
"Life's little spark."

168
00:11:57,860 --> 00:11:59,464
It made you guys millions.

169
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:00,701
Hold on a second.

170
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:02,510
That was a team effort.

171
00:12:02,740 --> 00:12:04,708
A team effort?
You're kidding, right?

172
00:12:04,940 --> 00:12:07,944
We both know that was my slogan.

173
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:10,581
It was 2 A.M., I was 17 years old

174
00:12:10,820 --> 00:12:13,664
I brought you guys coffee
and you were exhausted.

175
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:17,871
And I said, "Hey, where's the spark?
Life's little spark."

176
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:19,670
You loved it, Javier.

177
00:12:19,900 --> 00:12:22,107
You loved it.
Layout don't remember,

178
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:24,388
please, go and ask David.

179
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:28,029
I swear on my kids
that was mine.

180
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:29,861
I swear.

181
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:35,266
I'm sorry to put you on the spot
like this.

182
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:37,905
Thanks, Javier.

183
00:12:42,060 --> 00:12:42,822
Roberto.

184
00:12:44,780 --> 00:12:47,431
Maybe we could get your kid
a scholarship.

185
00:12:47,860 --> 00:12:48,941
Sure.

186
00:13:06,140 --> 00:13:08,427
Excuse me, can you spare any change
for a sandwich?

187
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:10,230
Sorry, I haven't got anything.

188
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:12,940
What do you mean?
You have a car

189
00:13:13,180 --> 00:13:14,341
and a briefcase and a house.

190
00:13:14,580 --> 00:13:17,265
You guys in ties are all bastards!

191
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:06,988
You're listening to Migma Radio.

192
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:10,110
This song is dedicated
to all those assholes out there

193
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:13,264
who tried to fuck up my day
but failed.

194
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:17,061
The song is called:
You can all go to hell

195
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:18,631
What? What?

196
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:20,908
What are you looking at?
What?

197
00:14:21,140 --> 00:14:22,904
What's your problem, you clown?

198
00:14:23,140 --> 00:14:23,902
What?

199
00:14:24,140 --> 00:14:26,029
Move it or l'll smash you.

200
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:29,503
You, you and you.All three of you.
Fucking kiss asses!

201
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:33,187
You want me to say it in English?
I'll say it in English.

202
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:34,387
Clown.

203
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:47,347
Can you give me the number
for the Hotel Paraiso in Cartage?

204
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:49,467
What?

205
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:52,661
It's not listed?
It has to be.

206
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:56,063
No, I don't want another hotel.
It has to be that one.

207
00:14:57,780 --> 00:14:59,270
Okay, never mind.

208
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:01,264
Thanks anyway.

209
00:15:01,780 --> 00:15:03,145
Goodbye.

210
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:34,981
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

211
00:15:35,220 --> 00:15:37,985
- Where's the hotel that was here?
- It's not here any more.

212
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:39,460
It’s gone.

213
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:42,348
These walls are over
two thousand years old.

214
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:45,504
Emperor Augustus would be proud
of the colossal undertaking

215
00:15:45,740 --> 00:15:48,107
initiated by City Hall

216
00:15:48,340 --> 00:15:51,901
to rescue this jewel of Imperial Rome
from the clutches of obscurity.

217
00:15:52,140 --> 00:15:55,189
Buried for centuries,
it remained hidden

218
00:15:55,420 --> 00:15:58,390
from human sight.
A coincidence, however,

219
00:15:58,660 --> 00:16:02,904
some boys playing with a Roman coin,

220
00:16:03,140 --> 00:16:06,110
caused the history of this city
to take

221
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:08,229
a 360-degree turn.

222
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:12,909
180. If you turn 360 degrees,
you end up in the same place.

223
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:14,587
Okay, then.

224
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:16,664
But a picture is worth

225
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:19,346
a thousand words.
Let's begin the guided tour.

226
00:16:19,740 --> 00:16:22,584
Here is our wonderful archeologist,

227
00:16:22,860 --> 00:16:24,271
Mercedes San Roman.

228
00:16:24,540 --> 00:16:27,544
She knows more than I do
about practically everything.

229
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,589
The first discoveries

230
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:36,471
were made under
the Plaza DE Condesa DE Peralta

231
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:39,351
when they started building
the Center for Arts and Crafts.

232
00:16:39,580 --> 00:16:41,423
- What about the coin?
- The mayor made that up.

233
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:44,823
The first digs uncovered
a complex alignment

234
00:16:45,060 --> 00:16:48,269
of structures
and rich architectural elements

235
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:51,788
which were a prelude
to the amazing archeological find

236
00:16:52,020 --> 00:16:54,261
which took place shortly thereafter.

237
