Jose! Jose, listen to me.

350
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:37,826
- Don't close, there was an accident.
- No, you're mistaken.

351
00:22:38,060 --> 00:22:40,904
That still hasn't been established.

352
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:44,030
- We're ruined!
- This is no time to joke,

353
00:22:44,260 --> 00:22:45,705
- Mayor.
- I'm not joking.

354
00:22:45,940 --> 00:22:48,022
This is horrendous.

355
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,509
Everything was so grandiose...

356
00:22:50,740 --> 00:22:52,504
All the photographers...
Everybody out!

357
00:22:52,820 --> 00:22:54,060
Get out of here!

358
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:56,749
Please, step back!

359
00:22:57,940 --> 00:22:59,783
<i>Please! He fell.</i>

360
00:23:01,940 --> 00:23:04,227
He fell. Please!

361
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,143
Everyone step back!
Coming through!

362
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:18,869
- Over here.
- Everyone step back.

363
00:23:20,820 --> 00:23:21,901
Hi.

364
00:23:22,140 --> 00:23:25,428
How's it going?
I'm Carlos, Toni and Pace, okay?

365
00:23:25,660 --> 00:23:26,786
Roberto.
Nice to meet you.

366
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:31,025
Toni's going to check your vitals
and I'll take a look under there.

367
00:23:31,260 --> 00:23:32,546
- Okay.
- Let's see.

368
00:23:34,940 --> 00:23:38,626
Roberto, any trouble breathing?
Any chest pain?

369
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:41,227
No, not my chest.
But my head hurts.

370
00:23:41,660 --> 00:23:43,628
Well, that's normal.

371
00:23:43,860 --> 00:23:46,591
Don't worry. Can you move your arms
and legs at the same time?

372
00:23:46,820 --> 00:23:48,982
Of course he can He just did.

373
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:51,541
- Let him say it.
- Yeah, I think so

374
00:23:51,780 --> 00:23:53,111
Blood pressure 130 over 85.

375
00:23:53,340 --> 00:23:54,387
Isn't that high?

376
00:23:54,620 --> 00:23:56,622
- You should see mine.
- Would you be quiet?

377
00:23:56,860 --> 00:23:58,703
Roberto, it's perfect, okay?

378
00:23:58,940 --> 00:24:00,146
What happened to your face?

379
00:24:00,620 --> 00:24:03,590
Nothing, a drunk guy punched me.
Who's in charge here?

380
00:24:04,020 --> 00:24:05,545
I'm the museum director.

381
00:24:05,780 --> 00:24:07,748
Can I have a word with you?
Come with me.

382
00:24:07,980 --> 00:24:10,506
Please, step back.
Step back!

383
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:12,151
Quit moaning!

384
00:24:12,740 --> 00:24:14,265
I can't move that man.

385
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:16,741
Take him away in the ambulance
right now.

386
00:24:16,980 --> 00:24:18,470
Will you take responsibility?
I won't.

387
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:19,747
I didn't say that

388
00:24:19,980 --> 00:24:21,266
He doesn't work here.

389
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:22,501
I know.

390
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,265
What were you doing, shithead?

391
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:26,222
Why can't you move him?

392
00:24:26,460 --> 00:24:29,782
That rod in his head
may have reached the brain.

393
00:24:30,020 --> 00:24:33,342
He could bleed to death
before we get to the hospital.

394
00:24:33,580 --> 00:24:34,149
Oh, my God.

395
00:24:34,380 --> 00:24:38,351
Are you a doctor? No, right?
Let the doctors make conclusions.

396
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:41,584
Take your ambulance
and get him out of here

397
00:24:41,820 --> 00:24:43,584
I'm not touching him.

398
00:24:43,820 --> 00:24:45,902
I told you it was too soon
to open to the public.

399
00:24:46,140 --> 00:24:47,744
I saw something like this once.

400
00:24:47,980 --> 00:24:49,744
A guy with a knife stuck
in his head.

401
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:50,902
Are you retarded?

402
00:24:51,140 --> 00:24:51,982
And?

403
00:24:52,540 --> 00:24:53,905
He died.

404
00:24:54,140 --> 00:24:54,982
What a schmuck.

405
00:24:55,220 --> 00:24:56,790
How could this happen?

406
00:24:57,020 --> 00:25:00,024
He grabbed the statue
and the crane spun around.

407
00:25:00,260 --> 00:25:01,750
I tried to stop him, but...

408
00:25:01,980 --> 00:25:03,505
What the hell are we paying you for?

409
00:25:03,780 --> 00:25:05,384
It's not his fault.

410
00:25:06,180 --> 00:25:07,341
I shouldn’t be here.

411
00:25:07,940 --> 00:25:09,271
Did the ?oor fall in?

412
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:12,191
I only wanted to come back
the hotel

413
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:14,184
where I spent my honeymoon.

414
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:17,708
Roberto, the fire department
will be here any minute.

415
00:25:29,980 --> 00:25:31,664
Make way, please!

416
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:33,345
Let'; go, let's go!

417
00:25:34,180 --> 00:25:36,148
Don't step there!

418
00:25:38,580 --> 00:25:40,025
Careful, damn it!

419
00:25:45,260 --> 00:25:48,946
If I cut the bar it'll shake too much
We have to make a hole.

420
00:25:49,180 --> 00:25:50,625
Let's get this straight.

421
00:25:50,860 --> 00:25:53,227
You're standing on national heritage.

422
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:55,189
You know what that means?

423
00:25:55,420 --> 00:25:57,104
You need an expert to dig here.

424
00:25:57,340 --> 00:25:59,342
Saving that man is the priority.

425
00:25:59,580 --> 00:26:01,708
That's yours, mine is the museum.

426
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:03,465
Layout don't let me work

427
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:05,862
Everybody settle down.
Don't be stupid.

428
00:26:06,100 --> 00:26:08,831
Can't we just raise him
a little bit?

429
00:26:09,060 --> 00:26:10,949
I'm afraid to move him.
We need a doctor.

430
00:26:11,180 --> 00:26:12,102
Roberto, right hand.

431
00:26:13,020 --> 00:26:14,260
Left hand.

432
00:26:14,780 --> 00:26:18,102
Roberto, I'm going to insert an IV.
You'll feel a prick.

433
00:26:21,180 --> 00:26:22,181
Don't cry, it doesn't hurt.

434
00:26:22,420 --> 00:26:25,105
You won't believe it,
but that hurt more than this.

435
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:27,831
Please, let me through.

436
00:26:29,300 --> 00:26:32,031
Roberto, we called a doctor
to examine you.

437
00:26:32,260 --> 00:26:34,467
We don't want to move you
until he's seen the rod.

438
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:38,341
I feel perfectly fine.
I don't know why we can't leave.

439
00:26:38,580 --> 00:26:41,231
It's not that simple.
We have to wait for the doctor.

440
00:26:41,460 --> 00:26:42,950
I need to call my wife.

441
00:26:43,180 --> 00:26:46,104
I told her you were taking me
to the hospital.

442
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:50,742
Yes?

443
00:26:50,980 --> 00:26:51,503
Hi, sweetie.

444
00:26:51,740 --> 00:26:53,230
I'm almost there.
What's wrong?

445
00:26:53,460 --> 00:26:54,586
I'm not going to the hospital.

446
00:26:54,820 --> 00:26:55,707
Then where?

447
00:26:55,940 --> 00:26:56,668
Nowhere.

448
00:26:56,900 --> 00:26:58,061
Why? What's going on?

449
00:26:58,300 --> 00:26:59,586
They're waiting for the doctor.

450
00:26:59,820 --> 00:27:00,821
Where are you?

451
00:27:01,060 --> 00:27:01,822
At the hotel.

452
00:27:02,060 --> 00:27:03,505
Our hotel?

453
00:27:03,740 --> 00:27:06,266
Well, it's a museum now.
It's incredible.

454
00:27:06,980 --> 00:27:09,187
They found a Roman theater
underneath it.

455
00:27:09,420 --> 00:27:11,104
What are you doing there?

456
00:27:11,340 --> 00:27:13,786
I was upset.
I wanted to get out of Madrid.

457
00:27:14,020 --> 00:27:17,661
I put the music on full blast
and I wanted to surprise you.

458
00:27:18,100 --> 00:27:20,671
It would have been nice
to spend our anniversary together.

459
00:27:20,900 --> 00:27:22,470
I'm almost there, my love.

460
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:25,271
Drive slowly, okay?
I don't want you to have an accident.

461
00:27:26,580 --> 00:27:28,628
I'll be there very soon

462
00:27:30,380 --> 00:27:32,223
She's a teacher.

463
00:27:32,460 --> 00:27:35,350
She loves working with kids.
That's why she puts up with me

464
00:27:35,580 --> 00:27:38,743
I had a girlfriend who dumped me
because I snore.

465
00:27:38,980 --> 00:27:41,221
- I never got to sleep with her.
- How did she know you snore?

466
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:42,427
You're right.

467
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:44,025
A friend must have told her.

468
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:46,222
Roberto!

469
00:27:46,460 --> 00:27:47,063
Roberto!

470
00:27:54,660 --> 00:27:56,185
Yeah, I'm okay.

471
00:27:59,540 --> 00:28:01,827
- My God.
- It's on the internet.

472
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:03,585
They'll destroy the theater.

473
00:28:03,820 --> 00:28:06,983
Years numbering every rock,
wrecked in minutes.

474
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:10,542
They'll sink my career in politics.
What do we do, Merche?

475
00:28:10,780 --> 00:28:12,464
Don't let them in!

476
00:28:55,300 --> 00:28:56,187
It's complicated.

477
00:28:57,300 --> 00:28:58,825
I'm listening, sorry.

478
00:29:02,300 --> 00:29:03,711
I can't talk right now!

479
00:29:16,820 --> 00:29:18,470
This way, doctor.

480
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:20,825
Please!

481
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:22,909
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

482
00:29:23,140 --> 00:29:25,507
- I'm Doctor Andres Velasco.
- Nice to meet you. Roberto.

483
00:29:25,740 --> 00:29:28,107
- Having a rough day, are we?
- Awful.

484
00:29:28,340 --> 00:29:29,865
Has he been conscious
the whole time?

485
00:29:30,100 --> 00:29:31,829
- Yes.
- Blood pressure 130 over 85.

486
00:29:32,060 --> 00:29:34,950
Doctor, tell us what's happening!
What's his name?

487
00:29:35,180 --> 00:29:37,387
Can we put up a screen or something?

488
00:29:37,620 --> 00:29:39,031
It's on the way.

489
00:29:39,260 --> 00:29:40,466
- Thank you, doctor.
- Roberto.

490
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:41,861
I'm going to perform
a neurological exam.

491
00:29:42,100 --> 00:29:44,910
Okay. Is this covered
by Social Security?

492
00:29:45,140 --> 00:29:47,063
Don't think about that now.
Relax, this won't hurt.

493
00:29:47,300 --> 00:29:50,588
I feel perfectly fine,
except for the rod.

494
00:29:57,700 --> 00:29:59,828
Roberto, can you feel my hand?

495
00:30:00,060 --> 00:30:00,868
Yes.

496
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:02,784
- Can you squeeze it?
- Sure.

497
00:30:03,020 --> 00:30:04,021
A little more.

498
00:30:04,260 --> 00:30:05,182
Very good.

499
00:30:05,420 --> 00:30:06,945
Stick out your tongue

500
00:30:07,620 --> 00:30:10,430
Very good, Roberto.
Let's see.

501
00:30:10,660 --> 00:30:12,424
Follow the light with your eyes.

502
00:30:12,660 --> 00:30:13,468
A little more.

503
00:30:15,300 --> 00:30:16,267
Very good.

504
00:30:17,260 --> 00:30:19,740
- Everything is fine
- Thank God.

505
00:30:19,980 --> 00:30:21,744
That's a relief.

506
00:30:31,060 --> 00:30:32,869
No questions, please!

507
00:30:33,300 --> 00:30:35,109
The patient is stable,

508
00:30:35,340 --> 00:30:37,820
but he can't be moved
until we see the X-rays.

509
00:30:38,060 --> 00:30:40,870
Would you blame the accident
on the poor conditions

510
00:30:41,100 --> 00:30:42,431
of the facility?

511
00:30:42,660 --> 00:30:44,583
He can't say any more.
He doesn't know.

512
00:30:44,820 --> 00:30:45,707
Thank you.

513
00:30:51,940 --> 00:30:53,783
- Claudio.
- What is it, Roberto?

514
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:56,591
- You think I'll be okay?
- Of course you will.

515
00:30:56,820 --> 00:30:58,470
I've seen much worse cases.

516
00:30:58,700 --> 00:31:00,782
My grandfather had a bullet
in his head from the war

517
00:31:01,020 --> 00:31:02,943
and he died old and happy.

518
00:31:03,220 --> 00:31:06,110
- I need you to hold your breath
- Sorry.

519
00:31:06,340 --> 00:31:07,466
One moment.

520
00:31:07,980 --> 00:31:08,981
Okay, thanks.

521
00:31:09,220 --> 00:31:10,460
It's funny.

522
00:31:11,060 --> 00:31:12,903
This morning nobody
wanted to talk to me

523
00:31:13,140 --> 00:31:15,950
- and now suddenly...
- It's everywhere on TV.

524
00:31:16,300 --> 00:31:18,780
You're going to be a star.

525
00:31:38,140 --> 00:31:39,221
Hey, where are you going?

526
00:31:39,460 --> 00:31:43,260
I'm Luisa Gomez. I need to see
my husband, he had an accident.

527
00:31:43,500 --> 00:31:46,071
