00:54:32,020 --> 00:54:35,183
We still don't know exactly
what happened,

1039
00:54:35,420 --> 00:54:38,583
but what we do know is
the victim's name is Roberto Gomez

1040
00:54:38,820 --> 00:54:41,107
and that he's an unemployed
advertising executive.

1041
00:54:41,380 --> 00:54:44,270
Tomorrow's headlines
lead with Roberto Gomez,

1042
00:54:44,500 --> 00:54:48,391
who might have tried to kill himself
because he's out of work.

1043
00:54:48,620 --> 00:54:50,941
Yousto Mafeo,
an awful crisis-related story.

1044
00:54:51,180 --> 00:54:53,103
Yes, shock and concern
across the media.

1045
00:54:53,340 --> 00:54:55,547
It's on the cover of every paper.

1046
00:54:55,780 --> 00:54:59,546
El Pais begins with: "Fatal accident
at Roman theater in Cartage"

1047
00:54:59,780 --> 00:55:01,828
and a photo of Roberto Gomez.

1048
00:55:02,060 --> 00:55:03,789
The Vanguardia also has a photo:

1049
00:55:04,020 --> 00:55:07,467
"Roberto Gomez suffers terrible accident
at Roman theater in Cartage."

1050
00:55:07,700 --> 00:55:11,500
A large photo in the ABC:
"Accident or suicide?"

1051
00:55:11,740 --> 00:55:12,582
Also international news...

1052
00:55:12,820 --> 00:55:13,821
We're screwed.

1053
00:55:14,140 --> 00:55:15,187
Wild, isn't it?

1054
00:55:15,460 --> 00:55:17,747
- He was here this morning
- I know.

1055
00:55:17,980 --> 00:55:20,745
He came to my office, but I was busy
with the expense account...

1056
00:55:20,980 --> 00:55:22,505
The bastard tried to kill himself.

1057
00:55:22,740 --> 00:55:24,788
- Fucking hell.
- You can't blame him

1058
00:55:25,020 --> 00:55:26,306
What did he say?

1059
00:55:26,540 --> 00:55:29,225
You know I'm up to my ears
with the Citroen campaign.

1060
00:55:29,460 --> 00:55:32,191
This could cause irreparable damage
The news has gone global.

1061
00:55:32,420 --> 00:55:34,787
If headquarters hears about this

1062
00:55:35,020 --> 00:55:35,862
we're screwed.

1063
00:55:36,100 --> 00:55:37,511
We have nothing to do with it.

1064
00:55:37,740 --> 00:55:40,823
