00:57:48,540 --> 00:57:49,427
Nothing.

1114
00:57:49,900 --> 00:57:52,870
- It's not as bad as it looks.
- What were you doing here?

1115
00:57:53,100 --> 00:57:55,990
I wanted your mother to see it.
Isn't it amazing?

1116
00:57:56,220 --> 00:57:57,984
It's so well-conserved.

1117
00:57:58,740 --> 00:58:02,381
I'm on Rumore, Rumore tonight.
How about that!

1118
00:58:02,740 --> 00:58:05,789
What do the doctors say?
Why are you still lying there?

1119
00:58:06,020 --> 00:58:09,024
They say I'll be fine.
You shouldn't have come, son

1120
00:58:09,260 --> 00:58:10,500
He shouldn't have come?

1121
00:58:11,420 --> 00:58:12,421
Lorenzo,

1122
00:58:12,660 --> 00:58:14,503
your father's situation
is serious.

1123
00:58:14,740 --> 00:58:16,868
They haven't moved him
because they don't know how.

1124
00:58:17,100 --> 00:58:18,943
Take your mother for a drink

1125
00:58:19,180 --> 00:58:21,228
- Does Barbara know?
- Yes, she's on her way.

1126
00:58:21,460 --> 00:58:23,622
- How is everything, Roberto?
- I'm okay.

1127
00:58:24,620 --> 00:58:26,145
You must be Doctor Sanz.

1128
00:58:26,780 --> 00:58:28,862
I'm Luisa Gomez, Roberto's wife.

1129
00:58:29,100 --> 00:58:31,341
Mrs. Gomez,
we'll do everything we can

1130
00:58:31,580 --> 00:58:33,184
to free your husband.

1131
00:58:33,420 --> 00:58:34,910
- Your son?
- Yes.

1132
00:58:35,180 --> 00:58:37,023
Andres Velasco, chief surgeon.

1133
00:58:37,260 --> 00:58:38,466
Lorenzo, creepy goth.

1134
00:58:40,220 --> 00:58:43,542
Go get something to drink. If anything
happens, Claudio will come find you.

1135
00:58:43,780 --> 00:58:46,101
There's a cafeteria by the museum.
I have lunch there.

1136
00:58:46,380 --> 00:58:48,189
It took my husband
a year and a half to find a job

1137
00:58:48,420 --> 00:58:51,708
They should ban this stuff on TV.
A man in agony...

1138
00:58:51,940 --> 00:58:55,262
Imagine his family
watching him die on TV.

1139
00:59:11,060 --> 00:59:13,142
You think Dad will be okay?

1140
00:59:14,380 --> 00:59:16,223
Of course he will.

1141
00:59:16,620 --> 00:59:18,702
You know your father.

1142
00:59:18,940 --> 00:59:22,626
He fell off a crane
and didn't break a single bone.

1143
00:59:22,860 --> 00:59:24,988
He's got a rod stuck in his head

1144
00:59:25,220 --> 00:59:29,066
and there he is, wheeling and dealing
like nothing's wrong.

1145
00:59:29,700 --> 00:59:31,828
- Your dad's very strong.
- Yeah.

1146
00:59:36,460 --> 00:59:37,985
Listen to me, Lorenzo.

1147
00:59:38,420 --> 00:59:40,263
Your dad will make it
through this.

1148
00:59:41,220 --> 00:59:42,710
Everything will be fine.

1149
00:59:45,900 --> 00:59:47,026
Excuse me,

1150
00:59:47,380 --> 00:59:49,348
there's no smoking in here.

1151
00:59:53,420 --> 00:59:54,865
