1152
00:59:55,100 --> 00:59:57,102
There's no smoking in here.

1153
00:59:57,460 --> 00:59:58,347
Mom...

1154
01:00:03,500 --> 01:00:04,990
Check, please.

1155
01:00:05,220 --> 01:00:07,746
I want your interview
on every channel.

1156
01:00:07,980 --> 01:00:10,347
- What about Rumore Rumore?
- It's screwed.

1157
01:00:10,580 --> 01:00:13,186
You said they offered 150 thousand

1158
01:00:13,420 --> 01:00:16,151
Yeah, but we can't accept
just anything right now.

1159
01:00:16,980 --> 01:00:18,664
The news has gone global.

1160
01:00:18,900 --> 01:00:21,949
Like the Chilean miners.
They lived and they're filthy rich.

1161
01:00:22,300 --> 01:00:26,350
Johnny, I'm only thinking of my family.
Don't lower the price.

1162
01:00:26,580 --> 01:00:28,105
Don't worry, I set a minimum.

1163
01:00:29,220 --> 01:00:32,349
Warner Bros. called
to ask about the movie rights.

1164
01:00:32,580 --> 01:00:34,025
- Yeah?
- And the video game.

1165
01:00:34,260 --> 01:00:38,026
I don't know how they'll make this
into a video game, but they're on it.

1166
01:00:38,260 --> 01:00:39,386
How much will they pay?

1167
01:00:39,620 --> 01:00:41,031
I'll ask them

1168
01:00:41,820 --> 01:00:43,231
Johnny speaking.

1169
01:00:43,500 --> 01:00:44,547
Hi, Kiko.

1170
01:00:45,780 --> 01:00:46,667
Yeah.

1171
01:00:49,420 --> 01:00:51,991
A movie.
Wouldn't that be nice?

1172
01:00:52,220 --> 01:00:53,585
It sure would, Claudio

1173
01:00:53,860 --> 01:00:56,067
I wonder how much they'd pay
for something like that.

1174
01:00:56,380 --> 01:00:58,986
Hey, who could play me?

1175
01:00:59,220 --> 01:01:00,107
Brad Pitt?

1176
01:01:00,340 --> 01:01:01,785
How about George Clooney?

1177
01:01:02,020 --> 01:01:03,351
Isn't he too old?

1178
01:01:03,660 --> 01:01:07,221
Yes, sir. He'll be out within an hour.
I guarantee it.

1179
01:01:07,460 --> 01:01:10,748
You don't get it. We don't want him
to leave now. There's no hurry.

1180
01:01:10,980 --> 01:01:12,186
But earlier you said...

1181
01:01:12,420 --> 01:01:13,546
Forget what I said.

1182
01:01:13,780 --> 01:01:17,830
Our theater is on every
international news channel

1183
01:01:18,060 --> 01:01:22,270
Do you realize how much money
that could mean for tourism?

1184
01:01:22,580 --> 01:01:24,070
I can't stop it.

1185
01:01:24,300 --> 01:01:26,064
You're not stupid,
you'll find a way.

1186
01:01:26,660 --> 01:01:28,822
Roberto, how are you?

1187
01:01:29,060 --> 01:01:30,471
Great, David.
What brings you here?

1188
01:01:30,700 --> 01:01:33,385
Hey, sorry I couldn't see you
this morning.

1189
01:01:33,620 --> 01:01:36,749
Gandara has us all on the Citroen
project. You know what that's like

1190
01:01:36,980 --> 01:01:39,551
That's okay, I understand.

1191
01:01:39,780 --> 01:01:41,589
It was my secretary's fault.
I'll fire her if you want.

1192
01:01:41,820 --> 01:01:43,345
No, no, please.

1193
01:01:44,300 --> 01:01:46,462
Listen, we're in a bind.

1194
01:01:46,900 --> 01:01:48,982
Javier was wondering

1195
01:01:49,220 --> 01:01:53,191
if you want to come work for us.
When you get out of here, of course.

1196
01:01:53,540 --> 01:01:56,942
That's funny, this morning
he said just the opposite.

1197
01:01:58,100 --> 01:01:58,987
Right.

1198
01:02:01,940 --> 01:02:04,546
The thing is, this just came up.

1199
01:02:04,820 --> 01:02:08,108
Martin, the kid I had lunch with,
is leaving.

1200
01:02:08,340 --> 01:02:09,705
Yeah? Where to?

1201
01:02:09,940 --> 01:02:12,830
I don't know.
Like I said, it was sudden.

1202
01:02:17,700 --> 01:02:20,624
How would it work? Would I take his spot
or would I work for you?

1203
01:02:21,180 --> 01:02:23,865
No, no, you'd be on your own.

1204
01:02:24,100 --> 01:02:26,023
You created "Life's little spark."

1205
01:02:26,260 --> 01:02:28,103
No, that was a team effort.

1206
01:02:28,340 --> 01:02:29,830
A team effort, but

1207
01:02:31,100 --> 01:02:31,987
Roberto...

1208
01:02:32,580 --> 01:02:34,947
Roberto, what's wrong?
Hey! Hey!

1209
01:02:35,260 --> 01:02:36,500
- Hey...
- Doctor!

1210
01:02:36,740 --> 01:02:37,502
Doctor!

1211
01:02:39,820 --> 01:02:41,026
Keep his head steady.

1212
01:02:42,300 --> 01:02:43,108
It's okay, Roberto.

1213
01:02:43,340 --> 01:02:44,501
You'll be fine

1214
01:02:44,740 --> 01:02:46,344
Twenty milligrams of Dilantin.

1215
01:02:46,580 --> 01:02:47,581
Okay, let's go.

1216
01:02:47,820 --> 01:02:49,106
What's wrong?

1217
01:02:49,340 --> 01:02:50,421
Twenty more!

1218
01:02:50,660 --> 01:02:51,582
Coming!

1219
01:02:55,660 --> 01:02:58,231
- Is that better?
- I'm better. I'll be okay.

1220
01:02:58,500 --> 01:03:00,264
I was shaking a little but...

1221
01:03:00,860 --> 01:03:01,907
What happened?

1222
01:03:02,140 --> 01:03:05,508
Nothing. He had a small seizure
and lost some spinal ?uid.

1223
01:03:05,740 --> 01:03:07,265
- What?
- Only a little.

1224
01:03:07,500 --> 01:03:08,228
Luisa.

1225
01:03:08,500 --> 01:03:09,581
Luisa.

1226
01:03:09,820 --> 01:03:11,424
David offered me a job.

1227
01:03:11,660 --> 01:03:12,263
Roberto,

1228
01:03:12,500 --> 01:03:15,504
Dr. Sanz and I have talked it over

1229
01:03:15,740 --> 01:03:17,868
and we'd like to bring in
a mobile operating room.

1230
01:03:18,100 --> 01:03:20,467
We've decided we can't risk
cutting the rod without

1231
01:03:20,700 --> 01:03:21,861
damaging your brain

1232
01:03:22,100 --> 01:03:23,989
Like bringing the hospital to him?

1233
01:03:24,220 --> 01:03:25,107
That's right.

1234
01:03:25,660 --> 01:03:26,661
And that works?

1235
01:03:26,900 --> 01:03:28,390
We think it's the best option.

1236
01:03:28,780 --> 01:03:32,102
It certainly is.
You can stay as long as you like.

1237
01:03:32,340 --> 01:03:34,183
We're here at the Roman theater
in Cartage

1238
01:03:34,420 --> 01:03:37,105
where Roberto Gomez,
an unemployed advertising executive,

1239
01:03:37,340 --> 01:03:40,549
got his head stuck on an iron rod
after jumping from a crane.

1240
01:03:40,780 --> 01:03:43,067
Doctors have called in
a mobile operating room

1241
01:03:43,300 --> 01:03:45,871
so they can free Mr. Gomez
from the iron rod

1242
01:03:46,100 --> 01:03:50,185
and move him immediately to the .R.
In hopes of saving him.

1243
01:03:50,580 --> 01:03:53,186
Lorenzo, go find David and tell him

1244
01:03:53,420 --> 01:03:54,706
I want to talk to him.

1245
01:03:58,660 --> 01:04:01,948
I'll make more money today
than in my whole lifetime.

1246
01:04:02,420 --> 01:04:06,061
And I'll put it in a college
trust fund for the kids.

1247
01:04:06,420 --> 01:04:08,263
And with what's left over,

1248
01:04:08,900 --> 01:04:12,188
we'll take the trip of our lives.
How about it?

1249
01:04:14,460 --> 01:04:15,382
Paris.

1250
01:04:16,020 --> 01:04:19,263
Paris, that's right.
Wishing we could all our lives

1251
01:04:19,500 --> 01:04:22,185
and we never got to go
But now...

1252
01:04:22,420 --> 01:04:25,071
There!
I'll get revenge on the banks.

1253
01:04:25,300 --> 01:04:28,190
You bounce one check
and those bastards

1254
01:04:28,420 --> 01:04:30,627
look at you like you're a criminal

1255
01:04:30,860 --> 01:04:34,706
I've had my bank account
with the same bank for 18 years

1256
01:04:35,020 --> 01:04:37,261
and when I missed
two mortgage payments

1257
01:04:37,500 --> 01:04:39,946
they treated me
like a fucking thief.

1258
01:04:40,180 --> 01:04:43,104
Bleeding me with commissions,
lying to <i>me...</i>

1259
01:04:43,340 --> 01:04:44,865
Sons of bitches!

1260
01:04:45,940 --> 01:04:47,544
You weren't like this before.

1261
01:04:47,780 --> 01:04:49,589
It's not fair, damn it.

1262
01:04:52,100 --> 01:04:55,991
Dad, David says he'll stick around,
but he doesn't want to disturb you.

1263
01:04:56,220 --> 01:04:59,459
Go tell him we'll sign
when this is over, okay?

1264
01:04:59,460 --> 01:05:00,700
Go tell him we'll sign
when this is over, okay?

1265
01:05:01,020 --> 01:05:01,942
Here.

1266
01:05:02,500 --> 01:05:06,471
Go pick up Barbara,
she should be at the station by now.

1267
01:05:07,540 --> 01:05:09,065
Be careful.

1268
01:05:09,660 --> 01:05:11,469
Honey, those boots...

1269
01:05:11,700 --> 01:05:13,270
How are we doing?

1270
01:05:13,500 --> 01:05:14,990
Johnny.

1271
01:05:15,420 --> 01:05:16,990
Got any news?

1272
01:05:17,300 --> 01:05:20,588
- We're a little stuck with Antena 5.
- What do you mean?

1273
01:05:20,820 --> 01:05:24,029
I can't get them on the phone.
They want to talk to my boss.

1274
01:05:24,260 --> 01:05:25,864
Then have your boss talk to them.

1275
01:05:26,100 --> 01:05:29,900
This is my deal. If I let them
go above me, I lose authority.

1276
01:05:30,140 --> 01:05:31,471
They'll never take me seriously.

1277
01:05:31,700 --> 01:05:33,907
What about the 150 thousand
minimum?

1278
01:05:34,140 --> 01:05:36,871
I want more.
150 thousand ain't shit.

1279
01:05:37,100 --> 01:05:39,182
Then no more Rumore Rumore?

1280
01:05:39,420 --> 01:05:41,991
No, no. That's a game
they love to play.

1281
01:05:42,220 --> 01:05:44,587
They're trying to scare us.

1282
01:05:44,820 --> 01:05:45,946
You know what Alvaro Aguirre said?

1283
01:05:46,180 --> 01:05:48,990
- Who?
- The head of Antena 5, darling.

1284
01:05:50,900 --> 01:05:52,390
What's going on?

1285
01:05:56,500 --> 01:05:59,982
He said he'd pay two million
if I can guarantee your husband's death.

1286
01:06:00,220 --> 01:06:01,710
